<h2 id="description">Description</h2>
<p>This is a short course on introducing first-order optimization methods, including proximal gradient descent, primal-dual splitting methods, alternating direction method of multipliers and Douglas-Rachford splitting methods. Some well-known accelerated algorithms are also introduced.</p>

